1209:The iter-029 lemmas materialise Step 1 (the abstract LES) and Step 2 (the corner-identification simp lemmas) of the iter-028 Serre-finiteness sketch (Section~\ref{sec:scheme_affineCoverMVSquare}); iter-030 materialised Step 2.5 (the toModuleKSheaf specialisation, a routine binding so downstream code paths can reference the LES on the structure sheaf of a curve directly); iter-031 materialised the \emph{source-object} half of Step 3 (the cover-totality identification at the sheaf level); iter-032 materialised the \emph{Ext-transport} half of Step 3 at universe $u+1$ (landing on $\HModule\,k\,F\,n$); iter-033 materialised the parallel \emph{Ext-transport} at universe $u$ (landing on $\Ext_u\,X_2\,F\,n$); iter-034 closed Step 3 by appending the Mathlib gap-fill $\Ext.\mathtt{chgUnivLinearEquiv}$ (universe-bump $\LinearEquiv$ upgrade of Mathlib's bare $\Equiv$ $\Ext.\mathtt{chgUniv}$) and composing iter-033 with it to produce the full bridge $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,T \equiv_{\Module k} \HModule\,k\,F\,n$ for terminal $T$; iter-035 closed Step 3.5 (the \emph{corner-bridge}) by specialising the iter-034 universal bridge to the $X_4$ corner of an $\AffineCoverMVSquare$ — both an abstract sheaf form (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_X4_linearEquiv}) and a curve specialisation (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_X4_linearEquiv_curve}); iter-036 appended the immediate \emph{finrank corollary} (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_finrank_HModule_eq_HModule_prime_X4} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_finrank_HModule_eq_HModule_prime_X4_curve}) — landing the genus carrier $\mathrm{finrank}_k\,(\HModule\,k\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,1)$ on the explicit corner $X_4$ via $\LinearEquiv.\mathtt{finrank\_eq}$; iter-037 appends the parallel \emph{$\Module.\mathtt{Finite}$ transport companion} (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_module_finite_HModule_of_HModule_prime_X4} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_module_finite_HModule_of_HModule_prime_X4_curve}) — the algebraic counterpart of iter-036, transporting finiteness rather than finrank across the corner-bridge, via Mathlib's $\Module.\mathtt{Finite.equiv}$. Iter-038 → iter-046 build the H⁰ Module.Finite ladder (curve specialisations + carrier predicates + Stein input + global-sections evaluation iso + producer chain end-to-end for $\IsHModuleHomFinite\,k\,C\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)$); iter-047 lays foundational parameterised Čech infrastructure; iter-048 appends the Čech-side acyclicity carrier predicate and abstract consumer; iter-049 appends the top-supremum HModule transport (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_isCechAcyclicCover_top} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_isCechAcyclicCover_top_curve}) — the universe $u \to u+1$ bridge that lets iter-053+ ultimately consume iter-048's $\Subsingleton$ on $\HModulePrime$ at the lattice supremum to derive the genus carrier $\Module.\mathtt{Finite}\,k\,(\HModule\,k\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,1)$ at universe $u+1$; iter-050 packages the Čech-vs-derived comparison iso as a $\Prop$-valued typeclass $\Scheme.\HasCechToHModuleIso$ with $\Classical.\mathtt{choice}$-based extractor (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_cechToHModuleIso}) and instance-driven \emph{top-supremum} consumers (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_top} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_top_curve}); iter-051 appends the symmetric instance-driven \emph{intermediate-supremum} consumers (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_supr_of_hasCechToHModuleIso} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_supr_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_curve}) — landing $\Subsingleton\,(\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,(\bigsqcup\mathcal U))$ at universe $u$; iter-052 (this iteration) appends the generalised rewrite-bridge $\bigsqcup\mathcal U = U$ consumers (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_of_hasCechToHModuleIso} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_curve}) — landing $\Subsingleton\,(\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,U)$ on an arbitrary open $U$ under the equality hypothesis, the exact form iter-054+ needs to instantiate $\IsAffineHModuleVanishing\,k\,C\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)$ for an affine open via a basic-open cover. The remaining work — Step 4 (the substantive Čech-vs-derived comparison theorem; iter-053+ multi-iteration; Mathlib has $\mathtt{cechComplexFunctor}$ but no comparison theorem; once landed as a theorem, an instance for $\HasCechToHModuleIso$ wraps it via $\langle\langle \mathtt{the\_iso}\rangle\rangle$) and Step 5 (basic-open cover acyclicity producers; iter-053+ computational; Koszul-like alternating-sum complex on localisations is exact) and Step 6 (assembling the genus carrier from the LES + iter-035/049 transport + Step 4/5 affine input) is iter-053+.

